Upon death of a member occurring while in service, arising from any cause other than in the performance of duty, provided the member has had at least five (5) years of total service, his or her surviving spouse shall receive an annuity equal to one and one-half percent (1-1/2%) of average salary for each year of total service, credited to the member, but not less than fifteen percent (15%) of average salary, subject to the following conditions:
The surviving spouse had been married to the member at least six (6) months prior to his or her death;
The surviving spouse's annuity will terminate in any event when the surviving spouse dies. The annuity of each child or children shall continue until each child attains age eighteen (18), or, in the case of a child regularly engaged in full-time educational activities the age of twenty-three (23).
